# Maintenance module

## Inspection form (`MaintenanceInspectionForm` and related)

- **Client**: `SearchableSelect`, not native `<select>`.
- **Sub-project**: searchable; optional when client has sub-projects; label **Sub-project (optional)**; empty **No sub-project**; single grid column (not `md:col-span-2`). API: `lib/clients/subProjectGate.ts` — optional even when rows exist; if an id is sent it must belong to the client.

### Door cards

- Header/dropdown: **serial-only** ids (`P0####`, legacy `PJ####`); do not repeat door type/extras in the dropdown label.

### Door details & history

- Optional blocks; avoid duplicating notes. Show previous history only when meaningful (no empty section by default).

### Checklist & notes UX

- Label text from maintained source (stable strings). Floating notes: real tooltip (hover + click; dismiss click-away/Escape).

### Photos (bulk upload)

- Avoid stale-prop races: append against latest photos (e.g. ref), not only `onChange([...photos, uploaded])`. **Offline**: keep behaviour safe (sequential OK); online may use limited concurrency.

### Downloads

- Show loading and progress (`Content-Length`) when possible; shared streaming helper with `onProgress`; disable button during download.

### Signature

- DPR-correct canvas (CSS vs backing store). Modes: draw; upload JPG/PNG/WebP; type (Roboto stack, few styles).

### AI rewrite (`app/api/ai/door-summary`)

- Editor behaviour: one defect per sentence; preserve detail; no assumptions; safety language only if stated. Refinement: send original + prior rewrite; if identical, one stronger retry; reduce randomness after first attempt.

### Rate limits (`lib/security/rateLimitDistributed.ts`)

- Do not use coarse per-IP buckets that starve AI routes; scope identifiers by path/feature where applicable.

